1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE JOINT
RESOLUTION 1091 By: Kendrix
4
5
6
7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Joint Resolution approving certain proposed
permanent rules of certain business and commerce
9 state agencies; excluding certain proposed permanent
rules of the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code
10 Commission; and directing distribution.
11
12
13 WHEREAS, pursuant to Section 308 of Title 75 of the Oklahoma
14 Statutes, the Oklahoma State Legislature shall adopt a joint
15 resolution to approve or disapprove administrative rules.
16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
17 AND THE SENATE OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
18 SECTION 1. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
19 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Accountancy Board filed on or before
20 February 1, 2026.
21 SECTION 2. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
22 permanent rules of the Alcoholic Beverage Laws Enforcement
23 Commission filed on or before February 1, 2026.
24
Req. No. 17228 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
2 permanent rules of the Board of Governors of the Licensed
3 Architects, Landscape Architects and Registered Commercial Interior
4 Designers of Oklahoma filed on or before February 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 4. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
6 permanent rules of the Construction Industries Board filed on or
7 before February 1, 2026.
8 SECTION 5. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
9 permanent rules of the State Board of Cosmetology and Barbering
10 filed on or before February 1, 2026.
11 SECTION 6. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
12 permanent rules of the State Board of Licensure for Professional
13 Engineers and Surveyors filed on or before February 1, 2026.
14 SECTION 7. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
15 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Horse Racing Commission filed on or
16 before February 1, 2026.
17 SECTION 8. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
18 permanent rules of the Insurance Department filed on or before
19 February 1, 2026.
20 SECTION 9. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
21 permanent rules of the Department of Labor filed on or before
22 February 1, 2026.
23
24
Req. No. 17228 Page 2

1 SECTION 10. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
2 permanent rules of the Oklahoma New Motor Vehicle Commission filed
3 on or before February 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 11. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
5 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Real Estate Commission filed on or
6 before February 1, 2026.
7 SECTION 12. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
8 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Tax Commission filed on or before
9 February 1, 2026.
10 SECTION 13. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
11 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission
12 filed on or before February 1, 2026 except the proposed changes in
13 Chapter 20 of Title 748 of the Oklahoma Administrative Code.
14 SECTION 14. The Oklahoma Secretary of State is hereby directed
15 to distribute copies of this resolution to the Governor and the
16 editor of "The Oklahoma Register".
